the miseries that the godlesse haue, operantur 〈◊〉 , they worke their owne destruction, and cuerlastyng perdition: sor they can not beare them as they ought to doe: they murmureThe 〈◊◊〉 of 〈◊◊〉 . and crye out agaynste god: but the godly whan he is in miseries he taketh greate profite by it, for miseries dryue hym to leaue synne and wickednes: and to repent for that which he hathe 〈◊〉 agaynste god. Here you maye perceiue nowe that they that wyll haue comforte muste goe to that pylgrimage, they must taste miseries, and so at the ende they shall haue euerlastyng comforte.
